subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitat.
Presumably tropical and subtropical moist broadleaf forests. Three species of small shrews—the Annamite White-toothed Shrew, the Taiwanese Gray White-toothed Shrew (
C. tanakae
), and the Hainan White-toothed Shrew (
C. wuchihensis
)—occur in Northern Annamite Rainforests Ecoregion 54.
